cs.NE, cs.SD, cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.IT. 

This paper deals with the analysis of human movements and the transmission of information during goal-directed movements. The use of real data and the focus on information theory suggest that cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a likely sub-category. The study of kinematics and the analysis of trajectories suggest that cs.SD (Software Development) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) are also possible sub-categories. The use of information theory and the communication analogy suggest that cs.IT (Information Theory) is a likely sub-category. Finally, the mention of Fitts' law suggests that cs.LG (Learning) is a possible sub-category as well.
